<HEAD>DE PONTE <HI>LONDINENSI</HI> Eju&s;&abque; Stupendo Situ &amp; Structur&acirc;, Ad <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">n&s;tar Celebris illius Hexa&s;tichi poetae <HI>Sannazarii</HI> de urbe <HI>Veneta</HI>&mdash;Viderat Hadriacis&mdash;</HEAD>
<LG>
<L>Cum <HI>Londinen&s;em</HI> Neptunus viderat Urbem,</L>
<L>Vectus ibi propriis at&abque; revectus aquis,</L>
<L>Dum den&s;am penetrat Syluam, Luco&s;&abque; ferentes</L>
<L>Pro ramis <HI>funes,</HI> pro folii&s;&abque; <HI>Cruces,</HI></L>
<L>Cum &s;uperimpo&s;itum Torrenti flumine <HI>Pontem</HI></L>
<L>Viderat, et rapido ponere jura freto,</L>
<L>Cum tantos muros, ferrumina, ca&s;tra, tot <HI>Arcus</HI></L>
<L>Vidit, &amp; haec tergo cuncta jacere &s;uo,</L>
<L><HI>Arcus,</HI> qui po&s;&s;ent totidem formare <HI>Rialtos</HI></L>
<L>Metiri &s;i quis &s;umma vel ima cupit;</L>
<L>Haec Deus undarum a&s;piciens, fluxu&s;&abque; retror &s;um</L>
<L>Tundere, &amp; horrendos inde boare Sonos,</L>
<L>Nunc mihi quanta velis Terrae miracula pandas</L>
<L>E&s;t primus Mundi <HI>Pons,</HI> ait, I&s;te <HI>Stupor.</HI></L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 LANG="eng" TYPE="version">
<PB REF="3">
<HEAD>The &s;ame paraphra&s;ed in <HI>Engli&s;h.</HI></HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">Of <HI>London-Bridg,</HI> and the Stupendous Site, and Structure thereof.</HEAD>
<LG>
<L>When <HI>Neptune</HI> from his billows <HI>London</HI> &s;pyde,</L>
<L>Brought proudly thither by a high Spring-Tyde;</L>
<L>As through a floating <HI>Wood</HI> He &s;teer'd along,</L>
<L>And dancing <HI>Ca&s;tles</HI> clu&s;ter'd in a throng;</L>
<L>When he beheld a mighty <HI>Bridg</HI> give law</L>
<L>Unto his Surges, and their fury awe;</L>
<L>When &s;uch a &s;helf of <HI>Cataracts</HI> did roar,</L>
<L>As if the <HI>Thames</HI> with <HI>Nile</HI> had changd her &s;hoar</L>
<L>When he &s;uch ma&s;&s;y Walls, &s;uch Towrs did eye,</L>
<L>Such Po&s;ts, &s;uch Irons upon his back to lye,</L>
<L>When &s;uch va&s;t <HI>Arches</HI> he ob&s;erv'd, that might</L>
<L>Nineteen <NOTE N="*" PLACE="marg">The prime Bridge in <HI>Venice.</HI></NOTE> Rialtos make for depth and height,</L>
<L>When the <HI>Cerulean God</HI> the&s;e things &s;urvayd,</L>
<L>He &s;hook his Trident, and a&s;toni&s;h'd &s;aid,</L>
<L>Let the whol Earth now all Her <HI>wonders</HI> count</L>
<L><HI>This Bridg of Wonders is the Paramount.</HI></L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
